RACE.RACE_TEXT: RETAMA PARK RACE 1 7F Dirt CR: 84. Allowance Purse 14000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 123 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CALIFORNIA SAND JS set a pressured pace while three wide then drew off into the turn, was in a long drive and held sway in the end. RB RATHOWAYNE was unhurried early and saving ground on the turn, rallied on the inside in the stretch and was gaining ground but was too late. RB HASHTAG was taken back off the pace while inside on the backstretch, rallied two wide and challenged for the lead at the top of the stretch then flattened out in the drive. WMA BIG BABY chased the early pace while two wide, dropped back before the turn and lacked a rally in the stretch. QUICK RAE AA was shuffled back at the start then allowed to settled and was no threat. UPTOWN RINGOFFIRE trailed throughout. Race was hand timed.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RETAMA PARK RACE 2 330 Y Dirt CR: 78. Maiden Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, AND FIVE YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 125 lbs.; Older, 128 lbs. For Paints and Appaloosas.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: WL CASANOVA bumped start, strong drive. VP COUNTRY SMOKE bore in, bumped, second best. VP SAVVY CHICK broke in, bumped hard. TEXAS MAGAZECHE bumped very hard, knocked sideways. RIOS ST DASH bumped, dropped back. A claim of foul was lodged by the trainer of TEXAS MAGAZECHE against the rider of VP SAVVY CHICK for interference at the start. A steward's inquiry was also held. After reviewing the film's, the steward's disqualified VP SAVVY CHICK from third and was placed fourth for interference at the start. This race was hand timed.
